					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Seems to record some provisions made for various services and food offerings to the goddess Śrīraṅga-nāyakiyār, apparently by Kandāḍai-Appaṅgār (vide No. 466 above), who is also assigned the donor's share of the offerings. Śrīraṅganārāyaṇapriyaṉ, the accountant of the temple figures as a signatory in the record.</p>						

						</summary>
